  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether the administration of allodepleted donor T
      cells to patients with haematological malignancies after stem cell transplant can improve the
      recovery of the patients immune system.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
